eted in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":24,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Gilbert de Saunford was born about 1200, in Great Hormead, Hertfordshire, England, United Kingdom, his father, John de Sanford, was 27 and his mother, Alice de Basset, was 21. He had at least 1 son and 2 daughters with Loretta la Zouche. He died in 1249, at the age of 50, and was buried in Earls Colne, Essex, England."},"et":{"Abt 1200–1249":"umbes 1200–1249","1200–1249":"1200–1249","1225–1271":"1225–1271","1211–1279":"1211–1279","1227–1278":"1227–1278","1230–1312":"1230–1312","1235–Male":"1235–Surnud","1174–1233":"1174–1233","1180–1224":"1180–1224","1230":"1230","1174":"1174","1271":"1271","1180":"1180","1227":"1227","1249":"1249","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1235":"1235","1312":"1312","1279":"1279","Abt 1200":"umbes 1200","1278":"1278","1233":"1233","1211":"1211","1200":"1200","about 1230":"umbes 1230","Great Hormead, Hertfordshire, England":"Great Hormead, Hertfordshire, England","Buckinghamshire, England":"Buckinghamshire, England","Earls Colne, Essex, England":"Earls Colne, Essex, England","Great Hormede, Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, England","Hertfordshire, England":"Hertfordshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1200–1249":"noin 1200–1249","1200–1249":"1200–1249","1225–1271":"1225–1271","1211–1279":"1211–1279","1227–1278":"1227–1278","1230–1312":"1230–1312","1235–Male":"1235–Kuollut","1174–1233":"1174–1233","1180–1224":"1180–1224","1230":"1230","1174":"1174","1271":"1271","1180":"1180","1227":"1227","1249":"1249","1215":"1